    :content
    "# vis-bridge\n\nPkg: `com.blockether/vis-bridge`. Src: `extensions/common/vis-bridge/`.\n\nSingle alias: `bridge/`.\n\n## v1 extraction/fill split\n\n```clojure\n(bridge/clojure-lsp-status)\n(def facts (bridge/extract-markdown \"docs/src/SUMMARY.md\"))\n(bridge/aggregate-rows facts) ; pure storage preview\n(bridge/fill! facts)          ; writes extension aggregates\n(bridge/extract-clojure {:project-root \".\"})\n```\n\nBridge v1 keeps language extraction separate from filling. Extractors under `bridge.languages.*` emit normalized facts; `bridge.core` maps facts to aggregate rows consistently and owns fill/reindex behavior. Markdown uses CommonMark; Clojure uses external `clojure-lsp dump`. Tree-sitter is deliberately not a v1 dependency.\n"}}}}
